TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.

Context("Numeric");

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$c2 = random(2,8,2);
$d2 = random(3,9,2);
$a2 = "2^($c2/$d2)";
$root2 = 2**(-1/$d2);
$b2 = round($root2*10000)/10000;
$r2 = round(($root2-1)*10000)/100;
$k2 = round(log($root2)/log(exp(1))*10000)/100;
$dec_r2 = round(($root2-1)*10000)/10000;
$dec_k2 = round(log($root2)/log(exp(1))*10000)/10000;


BEGIN_TEXT
Give the starting value ${BITALIC}a,${EITALIC} the growth/decay rate ${BITALIC}r,${EITALIC} and the continuous growth/decay rate ${BITALIC}k.${EITALIC}  If there is exponential is decay, then your growth rates should be entered as negative percents.  For help entering logarithms, see \{ AnswerFormatHelp("logarithms") \}
$BR
$BR
\( Q = 2^{-(t-$c2)/$d2} \) has:
$BR
$BR
\( a = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( r = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}$PERCENT (round to the nearest 0.01${PERCENT})
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( k = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}$PERCENT (round to the nearest 0.01${PERCENT})
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}

END_TEXT

ANS(Real("$a2")->cmp() );
ANS(Real("$r2")->cmp() );
ANS(Real("$k2")->cmp() );

#ANS(num_cmp($a2) );
