#ANS(num_cmp($k2) );

$power2 = 2**$c2;

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
We can use exponent rules to place this in the form \( ab^t \): $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ 2^{-(t-$c2)/$d2} = 2^{\left( -(1/$d2)(t-$c2) \right)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = 2^{\left( $c2/$d2-(1/3)t \right)} \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = 2^{$c2/$d2} \cdot 2^{(-(1/$d2)t) } \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = 2^{$c2/$d2} \cdot \left(2^{-1/$d2}\right)^t \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = \sqrt[$d2]{$power2} \cdot \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt[$d2]{2}} \right)^t \)
$BR $SPACE $BR


Writing this as \( Q = \sqrt[$d2]{$power2} \cdot \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt[$d2]{2}} \right)^t \), we have:
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ a= \sqrt[$d2]{$power2} \ \), $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b= \frac{1}{\sqrt[$d2]{2}} = \approx $b2 \ \), $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ r = b-1 \approx $dec_r2 \ \) or about $r2${PERCENT}, $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ k= \ln{b} = \ln{ \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt[$d2]{2}} \right)} \approx $dec_k2 \ \) or about $k2${PERCENT}
$BR
END_SOLUTION


